Adjust rack to top position (top and middle positions for 4 servings) and preheat oven to
450 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Cut @potatoes{12%ounces} into ½-inch-thick wedges. Halve, peel, and grate ¼ of the
@yellow onion{1}(halved, peeled, and grated ¼) on the largest holes of a
#box grater{}; cut remaining onion into ½-inch-thick wedges. Halve, core, and
thinly slice @bell pepper{1}(halved, cored, and thinly sliced into ½-inch-thick strips).

Toss potatoes on a lightly oiled #baking sheet{} with a large drizzle of @olive oil{2%teaspoons},
@garlic powder{1/2%teaspoon}, and a big pinch of @salt{pinch} and @pepper{}.

Roast on top rack until browned and tender, ~{20-25%minutes} (you'll add more to the
sheet after 5 minutes).

In a #medium bowl{}, gently combine @ground pork{10%ounces}, grated onion,
@dried oregano{1%teaspoon}, @panko breadcrumbs{1/4%cup}, @chicken stock concentrate{1},
half the @feta cheese{1/4%cup}, remaining @garlic powder{1/2%teaspoon}, @salt{1/2%tsp},
and @pepper{}.

Form into two 1-inch-tall meatloaves (four loaves for 4).

Once potatoes have roasted 5 minutes, remove baking sheet from oven. Carefully add
bell pepper and onion wedges to sheet; toss to combine. Season with a pinch of salt
and pepper.

Push veggies to one side of sheet. Place meatloaves on empty side and return sheet
to top rack. Roast until meatloaves are browned and cooked through and veggies are
tender, ~{18-22%minutes}.

> For 4 servings, leave potatoes roasting. Toss bell pepper and onion on one side
> of a second baking sheet and place meatloaves on empty side; roast on middle rack.

In a #small microwave-safe bowl{}, combine @Greek vinaigrette{1 1/2%oz} and
@marinara cup{2.5%oz}.

Microwave on high until warmed through, ~{30%seconds}.

Divide roasted veggies and meatloaves between plates. Sprinkle veggies with remaining
@feta cheese{1/4%cup}(crumbled) and drizzle meatloaves with as much tangy marinara
as you like. Serve.

> Ground Pork is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 160°.